<br><p>
Investing for a Goal at Least Five Years Away<br>
<br>
Our picks with an emphasis on total return<br>
<br>
Junk-bond funds continue to dominate our taxable picks for the investor willing to trade some risk for higher total returns. Through mid-November the group showed an average total return of 10.8 percent. On the tax-free front, long-term municipal funds have finally started to show some life. Their average yield of 4.8 percent is equal to a taxable yield of 7.95 percent for an investor in the 39.6 percent federal tax bracket. In the picks at right -- suitable for a long-term investor able to stomach sizable dips -- we equally emphasize 12-month yield, relative safety (the smallest three-month loss since 1990), and total return over a five-year period. 
 <br>
