				<font size=6><b>97/01S-Asset Allocation: Mixed Signals</b></font><br>
				<font size=4></font><p>
				</center>
				
				<blockquote>
					<center>
						<font size=4><b><i></i></b></font><p>
					</center>
					<font size=4>
						Action at last -- but not much clarity. Northern Trust shifted 7 percentage points of its portfolio from international to domestic equities, while Bessemer Trust reduced domestic stocks by 1.4 percentage points. The two other banks in our survey stood pat for the fourth month in a row.<p>
Brown Brothers
