**Update**<p>
The November 1995 "10 Stocks to Consider" selections by Jim Melcher, president of New York–based Balestra Capital, gained 37 percent in the 12 months ended September 18. Melcher's biggest winner was Telebras SA, which jumped 152 percent. In the same issue, the "<a HREF="http://www.worth.com/articles/Z9511N02.html">10 Stocks to Avoid</A> " selected by Edwin Vroom, founder of New York–based Roanoke Asset Management, underperformed the market, gaining 1.6 percent in the period. Advanced Micro Devices dropped the most: 59 percent. <p>

