<html>
	<head>
		<title> Worth OnLine - 96/04-10 Stocks to Consider/Avoid</title>
	</head>
	
	<body background="/imgs/goldbarsmooth.gif" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"
	      text="#000000" link="#FF0000" vlink="#BB0000"> 	
	<a name="#top">
	<table width=550 cellpadding=10 cellspacing=5>
	
	<tr>
		<td width=390 valign=top> 
		
		<a href=/cgi/ad-relay.cgi?http://www.pcfn.com/6015.html?worth+PCFN16.gif+Archives>
<img src="/ads/PCFN16.gif" border=3 width=372 height=45 alt="PC Financial Network"></a>


		</td>
		<td  width=150>
		<!-- empty cell -->
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
	<td width=390 valign=top>
		
		<center>
		<p>
		<b><a href="/index.html">Home</a>  |  <a href="/departments/departments.html">Departments</a>  |  <a href="/search/query.html">Search</a>  |  <a href="/forums/index.html">Message Boards</a></b>
		<pre>
		</pre>
				<font size=5><b>10 Stocks to Consider/Avoid</b></font><br>
				<font size=6><b>96/04-10 Stocks to Consider/Avoid</b></font><br>
				<font size=4></font><p>
				</center>
				
				<blockquote>
					<center>
						<font size=4><b><i></i></b></font><p>
					</center>
					<font size=4>
						April 1996 <p>Worth magazine/Need to Know  <p> 10 STOCKS TO CONSIDER, 10 STOCKS TO AVOID  <p> CLIFF HENRY, president of CWH Associates, a New York City investment firm, manages $25 million in two hedge funds, which returned 58 percent to investors in 1995 and have averaged 26 percent annually since 1990. His stocks to avoid are the also-rans insuch fast-growing industries as medical technology: companies too dependent on an outdated technology or too small to grab significant market share. For example, Henry believes that <a name="NYSE:SDG"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=16492"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>Sofamor Danek Group's</b></a> spinal implant device, which accounts for over 90 percent of sales, will be eclipsed by a superior product due out this year from Spine-Tech. <a name="NASD:CTSC"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=16940"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>Cellular Technical Services'</b></a> technology protects against cellular-phone fraud, but the company could lose market share when phones with built-in security chips from telecom giants such as <a name="NYSE:NOK.A"></a><b>Nokia</b> and <a name="NYSE:T"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=10103"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>AT&T</b></a> become widespread. <a name="NASD:PNDA"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=43104"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>Panda Project</b></a>makes a server with removable cards so users can upgrade easily. The product is unique, but Panda may lack the clout to capture enough share to survive in a market dominated by behemoths such as <a name="NASD:SUNW"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=14833"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>Sun Microsystems</b></a>. Although Matsushita will release <a name="NASD:THDO"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=16077"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>3DO's</b></a>'s new 64-bit video-game machine this fall, it may have trouble competing against leader Nintendo's new platform and programs. <p> CHIP MORRIS'S $2.3 billion <a name="FUND:PRSCX"></a><a href="http://www.investools.com/cgi-bin/Library/t_page.pl/worth/PRSCX"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>T. Rowe Price Science & Technology Fund</b></a> is coming off a good year: The fund was up 60.99 percent for the 12 months ended January 31, 1996, placing it second among all technology funds. Over five years, the fund has earned 28.73 percent annually. Morris looks for stocks that will appreciateby 30 percent within 9 to 18 months. A company must have original technology or products that have garnered high margins or market share, revenue and earnings growth of over 20 percent a year, a record of meeting annual earnings expectations, and new products that will result in growth not yet reflected in the stock price. Desktop-publishing-software leader <a name="NASD:ADBE"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=12518"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>Adobe Systems</b></a> took a hit duringt he fourth-quarter tech sell-off, when erratic quarterly profits drove its price-to-earnings ratio from the 50s to the 30s. Morris expects a rebound this year when Adobe issues updated products. <a name="NASD:PLAT"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=10452"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>Platinum Technology</b></a>is the leading provider of relational database software, a potential multibillion-dollar market by 2000. A successfulintegration of recent acquisitions could triple the stock price. Morris calls Vodafone the McCaw Cellular of Europe. Upgrades to its U.K. service should keep it a market leader there.  <p> Company -- fair value* <p>(Exchange, ticker symbol)  <p> CLIFF HENRY'S 10 TO AVOID <p>Cellular Technical Services$18 <p>(Nasdaq: CTSC) <p><a name="NASD:CHTL"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=45333"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>Chantal Pharmaceutical</b></a>  $2 <p>(Nasdaq: CHTL) <p><a name="NASD:CYRX"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=16430"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>Cyrix</b></a>  $17<p>(Nasdaq: CYRX)  <p><a name="NASD:ERTS"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=14059"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>Electronic Arts </b></a> $18 <p>(Nasdaq: ERTS) <p><a name="NASD:KOPN"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=15607"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>Kopin </b></a> $9 <p>(Nasdaq: KOPN) <p>Panda Project  $10 <p>(Nasdaq: PNDA) <p><a name="NASD:PIXR"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=46451"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>Pixar</b></a> $16 <p>(Nasdaq: PIXR) <p><a name="NASD:SCUR"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=47097"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>Secure Computing </b></a> $16 <p>(Nasdaq: SCUR) <p>Sofamor Danek Group  $22 <p>(NYSE: SDG) <p>3DO  $5 <p>(Nasdaq: THDO)  <p> CHIP MORRIS'S 10 TO CONSIDER <p>Adobe Systems  $40 <p>(Nasdaq: ADBE) <p><a name="NYSE:AZA"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=11677"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>Alza Corp. </b></a> $33  <p>(NYSE: AZA) <p><a name="NYSE:ADI"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=10112"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>Analog Devices </b></a> $35  <p>(NYSE: ADI) <p><a name="NASD:XPRT"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=43178"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>Expert Software </b></a> $15  <p>(Nasdaq: XPRT) <p><a name="NASD:MXIM"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=14048"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>Maxim Integrated Products</b></a>  $45 
(Nasdaq: MXIM) <p><a name="NYSE:NDC"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=14201"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>National Data Corp.</b></a>  $35  <p>(NYSE: NDC) <p><a name="NASD:OMPT"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=47791"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>Omnipoint </b></a> $25 <p>(Nasdaq: OMPT) <p>Platinum Technology  $15 <p>(Nasdaq: PLAT) <p><a name="NYSE:VOD"></a><b>Vodafone Group </b> $40 <p>(NYSE: VOD) <p><a name="NASD:XLNX"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=15245"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>Xilinx </b></a> $45 <p>(Nasdaq: XLNX)  <p> *Fair value is the purchase price each stock picker considers reasonable for his or her choices.   <p> UPDATE <p>William Nasgovitz, manager of the $1.3 billion <a name="FUND:HRTVX"></a><a href="http://www.investools.com/cgi-bin/Library/t_page.pl/worth/HRTVX"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>Heartland Value Fund</b></a> in Milwaukee, chose April 1995's "Ten Stocks to Consider" from his 240 holdings. His picks rose just 6.8 percent on average in the past 12 months, but he spotted three winners: Aequitron Medical, a maker of electronic health-care equipment, up 74 percent; Psicor, a provider of services needed in open-heart surgery, up 51 percent; and Spartech, a plastics maker, up 26 percent. Starcraft Automotive, a specialty body shop, fell 46 percent.<p><p>
KEYWORDS: Stock Investing, Mutual Funds Investing

