	<head>
		<title> Worth OnLine - 96/09-Trend Spotter</title>
	</head>
	
	<body background="/imgs/goldbarsmooth.gif" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"
	      text="#000000" link="#FF0000" vlink="#BB0000"> 	
	<a name="#top">
	<table width=550 cellpadding=10 cellspacing=5>
	
	<tr>
		<td width=390 valign=top> 
		
		<a href=/cgi/ad-relay.cgi?http://www.pcfn.com/6015.html?worth+PCFN16.gif+Archives>
<img src="/ads/PCFN16.gif" border=3 width=372 height=45 alt="PC Financial Network"></a>


		</td>
		<td  width=150>
		<!-- empty cell -->
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
	<td width=390 valign=top>
		
		<center>
		<p>
		<b><a href="/index.html">Home</a>  |  <a href="/departments/departments.html">Departments</a>  |  <a href="/search/query.html">Search</a>  |  <a href="/forums/index.html">Message Boards</a></b>
		<pre>
		</pre>
				<font size=5><b></b></font><br>
				<font size=6><b>96/09-Trend Spotter</b></font><br>
				<font size=4></font><p>
				</center>
				
				<blockquote>
					<center>
						<font size=4><b><i></i></b></font><p>
					</center>
					<font size=4>
						By Melissa Jeffries<p>DEAD RECKONING. Make sure your broker's got a calculator. According to a recent American Management Association survey, 32 percent of applicants for jobs in the financial sector are deficient in math and literacy skills.<p>COLLEGE BYTES. And you thought books were expensive? At certain schools, Junior must have his own hard drive to get a degree. "The computer is integral on campus," says Bill Brawley of Dartmouth College, where owning a PC is mandatory. Wake Forest University figures it into the bill.<p>LET'S GET A ROOM. There's good news for agoraphobic executives: New York's Waldorf-Astoria and the Capital Hilton in Washington, D.C., now offer virtual video-conferencing suites with big screens that broadcast real-time, life-size images of users. But at $199 per hour, it's one costly room with a view.<p>SECONDHAND SEDANS. Can't afford a brand-new Jag? Go used. The hottest new business among luxury-auto manufacturers is hawking their lease-is-up returns. Unlike typical pre-owned rides, these cars carry brand-new warranties and maintenance plans.<p>PINK-SLIP PARTIES. Getting fired could be cause for celebration. Outplacement firm Challenger, Gray & Christmas reports that 92.4 percent of recently laid-off executives and managers now earn just as much or more at their new jobs -- up from 86.1 percent in 1995. "Companies are in hot competition to hire the best people, and they're willing to pay," says president James Challenger. Who says long lunches don't pay off?<p><p><p>

					</font>
					<p>
		
		
		
</td><td width=150 valign=top>

<center>
		
	<a href="/index.html">
	<IMG SRC="/imgs/datalineyellow.gif" border=0 alt="Worth"></a><p>
</center>
<pre>


</pre>
					<tt><font size=+1>
					<center>
						<img src="/imgs/1page.gif"><br>About 1 page

					</font>
					</tt>
					</center>

					<pre>
					</pre>


					</font>
					<p>

					<p>

					<p>
	
		
</td>
	</tr>
