					</center>
					<font size=4>
						DAVID DREMAN believes in value --  he won't have anything to do with an "Internet company trading primarily on dreams." That approach helped drive year-to-date returns at his $126 million Kemper Dreman Small Cap Fund to 13 percent through July 17 and allowed the fund to outpace the Russell 2000 small-cap index by 15.2 percentage points in 1995. His studies have shown that value small caps outperform concept stocks over time. Dreman concentrates on small-company stocks (market capitalizations below $1 billion) with low p/e's relative to the market, rising dividends, and a solid financial history. He looks to hold on to stocks for one to three years. For example, the tiny stock of <a name="NASD:PRXM"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=15960"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>Proxima</b></a>, a manufacturer of desktop projectors for computers, should benefit from the introduction of a new product that beats the competition. With the completion of a potential acquisition, specialized metal manufacturer <a name="NYSE:NX"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=11239"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>Quanex</b></a> will reduce its vulnerability to economic cycles -- which has recently kept investors away. <a name="NYSE:SEI"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=12313"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>Seitel</b></a>, a provider of seismic data for the oil and gas industries, is developing a new gas-exploration business. <a name="NYSE:FJC"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=10551"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>Fedders</b></a>, the leading manufacturer of room air conditioners in the U.S., has expanded its business in China.<p><a name="NYSE:BLTA"></a><b>Blount International</b> (NYSE: BLTA) $31
* Good earnings growth
