				<blockquote>
					<center>
						<font size=4><b><i></i></b></font><p>
					</center>
					<font size=4>
						ROBERT BUETTNER signed on as co-manager of the <a name="FUND:LDNBX"></a><a href="http://www.investools.com/cgi-bin/Library/t_page.pl/worth/LDNBX"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>Lindner Bulwark Fund</b></a> in January 1996, the worst of times: The fund had finished 1995 trailing the Standard & Poor's 500 Stock Index by a whopping 51 percentage points. But thanks to the fund's recent success in picking stocks to short, 1996 has been very different -- through July 17, the fund had returned 31.4 percent versus the S&P's 3 percent. Buettner seeks stocks of companies with deteriorating balance sheets -- growing inventories, climbing accounts receivable, and high or increasing debt loads are three key indicators -- to short with a 9- to 12-month time horizon. When disappointing earnings further fuel short-term declines, he knows he's got a winner. Direct-mail marketer <a name="NYSE:AD"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=12490"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>ADVO</b></a> has taken on debt and laid off workers. After adding capacity, <a name="NYSE:BGG"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=10231"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>Briggs & Stratton</b></a>, the engine manufacturer, faces high depreciation charges and interest expenses in a sluggish market. Business-application-software developer <a name="NASD:SSAX"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=14863"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>System Software</b></a> has seen cash on hand fall more than 50 percent over the last year, and debt has mounted. <a name="NASD:TNSI"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=42014"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>Transaction Network Services</b></a>, a provider of transmission services for credit-card authorizations, faces increased competition from <a name="NYSE:T"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=10103"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>AT&T</b></a> and <a name="NASD:CSRV"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=43062"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>CompuServe</b></a>.<p>ADVO (NYSE: AD) $5.50
