	<tr>
	<td width=390 valign=top>
		
		<center>
		<p>
		<b><a href="/index.html">Home</a>  |  <a href="/departments/departments.html">Departments</a>  |  <a href="/search/query.html">Search</a>  |  <a href="/forums/index.html">Message Boards</a></b>
		<pre>
		</pre>
				<font size=5><b></b></font><br>
				<font size=6><b>96/08-10 Stocks to Avoid</b></font><br>
				<font size=4></font><p>
				</center>
				
				<blockquote>
					<center>
						<font size=4><b><i></i></b></font><p>
					</center>
					<font size=4>
						JOSEPH PARNES, president of Technomart Investment Advisors 
in Baltimore, has done better than most short-sellers during this market rally. The shorts recommended in his five-year-old investment newsletter, Shortex, returned 26.5 percent in 1995. (The $50 million he manages in accounts that invest both long and short earned 56.54 percent in 1995.) To find stocks to short, Parnes looks for heavy selling on falling stock prices and such deteriorating fundamentals as declining earnings and revenues. The stock of oil refiner <a name="NYSE:ASH"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=10135"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>Ashland</b></a> rose 34 percent in the past six months, but Parnes believes the run-up in oil prices is temporary, and big investors have been selling. Declining orders and profit margins at integrated-circuit maker <a name="NASD:LLTC"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=13973"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>Linear Technology</b></a> will continue to drive the stock's price down. The stock price of tobacco giant <a name="NYSE:MO"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=11179"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>Philip Morris</b></a> retreated 15 percent in one month on heavy selling; Parnes thinks the company faces substantial legal and regulatory threats. Perennial laggard <a name="NYSE:ZE"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=11660"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>Zenith Electronics</b></a> moved higher when investors learned of its plan to make modems that would connect TVs to the Internet over cable systems. But, says Parnes, the company has never made money, and its new product will face stiff competition. <p>
<a name="NYSE:AMD"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=10037"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>Advanced Micro Devices</b></a> 
(NYSE: AMD) Fair Value $13
* Declining earnings 
* High-cost producer 
* Competition is too tough <p>Ashland 
(NYSE: ASH) $30
* Unrealistic earnings expectations 
* Falling product prices in the offing
* Impending overcapacity<p><a name="ASE:FRX"></a><b>Forest Laboratories </b>
(ASE: FRX) $32
* Declining earnings 
* Costly new product
* Intense competition <p><a name="NYSE:GLX"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=41781"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>Glaxo Wellcome </b></a>
(NYSE: GLX) $16
* Pending loss of patent protection
* Dependent on patented products 
* Margins under pressure<p>Linear Technology 
(Nasdaq: LLTC) $24
* Overcapacity 
* Declining orders 
* Industry is in down cycle <p><a name="NYSE:MU"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=14116"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>Micron Technology </b></a> 
(NYSE: MU) $22
* Overcapacity
* Falling product prices 
* Industry is in down cycle <p><a name="NASD:CALL"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=10950"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>Nextel Communications</b></a> 
(Nasdaq: CALL) $13
* Outdated technology 
* Ongoing losses 
* Growing debt from acquisitions<p>Philip Morris 
(NYSE: MO) $75
* Potentially large legal liability 
* Potential regulatory problems
* Institutions likely to sell stock <p><a name="NASD:VJET"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=42104"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>ValuJet </b></a>
(Nasdaq: VJET) $8
* Heightened FAA monitoring 
* Cutting back expansion  
* Declining passenger load <p>Zenith Electronics
(NYSE: ZE) $8
* Unproven product
* Low barriers to entry 
* Stock price due to Internet mania <p><p>
KEYWORDS: Stock Investing Strategies

					</font>
					<p>
		
		
		
