				<font size=5><b></b></font><br>
				<font size=6><b>96/08-10 Stocks to Consider</b></font><br>
				<font size=4></font><p>
				</center>
				
				<blockquote>
					<center>
						<font size=4><b><i></i></b></font><p>
					</center>
					<font size=4>
						ED KEELY, manager of the $839 million large-cap <a name="FUND:FRGRX"></a><a href="http://www.investools.com/cgi-bin/Library/t_page.pl/worth/FRGRX"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>Founders Growth Fund</b></a>, returned 45.6 percent for 1995 and 15.3 percent for 1996 as of May 17. He looks for companies that can consistently beat analysts' estimates and that can increase earnings by 20 percent in the next 12 months. Since valuations are high, he's scooping up firms that have temporarily stumbled. For instance, <a name="NYSE:CCK"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=10419"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>Crown Cork & Seal</b></a>, the world's largest packager and can maker, took a hit from rising aluminum prices last year, but earnings should improve because of falling metal prices and the acquisition of European can company Carnaud MetalBox. <a name="NYSE:GIC"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=15718"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>General Instrument</b></a>'s stock fell when the company missed deadlines for bringing digital TV-set-top boxes to market. But this fall, volume shipping of the devices, which will provide more channels and access to the Internet, should lead to 18 percent growth. The stock of <a name="NASD:NELL"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=14223"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>Nellcor Puritan Bennett</b></a>, a provider of equipment and therapy to treat respiratory illness, tumbled because a new in-house sales force wasn't yet up to speed, but Keely thinks earnings growth will rebound to 20 percent. Internet hub maker <a name="NYSE:CS"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=10276"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>Cabletron Systems</b></a> is entering the hot market for switches--earnings could increase by 30 percent in the next eight months.<p>Cabletron Systems 
(NYSE: CS) Fair Value $105
* Launching new product
* Loyal customer base
* Rapid industry growth<p>Crown Cork & Seal 
(NYSE: CCK) $55
* Global market leader
* Cost of raw materials has dropped
* Profitable synergies from merger<p>General Instrument 
(NYSE: GIC) $45
* Global market leader
* Launching new product
* Strong international growth <p><a name="NYSE:HS"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=13876"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>Healthsource</b></a>  
(NYSE: HS) $36
* Expanding customer base 
* Growing through acquisitions
* Strong physician networks<p>Nellcor Puritan Bennett 
(Nasdaq: NELL) $62
* Improved sales force
* Ample acquisition prospects
* Strong international growth <p><a name="NASD:ORNGY"></a><b>Orange</b>  
(Nasdaq: ORNGY) $25
* Expanding customer base
* State-of-the-art products
* Rapid industry growth <p><a name="NYSE:SKS"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=40406"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>Saks Holdings </b></a>
(NYSE: SKS) $40
* Revitalized merchandise mix
* Able to expand in a tough market
* Consolidating industry <p><a name="NYSE:SIH"></a><b>Sun International Hotels</b>
(NYSE: SIH) $58
* Expanding existing properties
* Opening new casino in hot area
* Operational improvements <p><a name="NASD:USRX"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=15388"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>U.S. Robotics </b></a>
(Nasdaq: USRX) $120
* Big phone-company contracts 
* Quality, low-cost manufacturer
* Entering new market <p><a name="NASD:XLNX"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=15245"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>Xilinx </b></a>
(Nasdaq: XLNX) $55
* Proprietary products 
* Consistent financial performance
* Rapid industry growth <p><p>
KEYWORDS: Mutual Funds Investing, Stock Investing Strategies

					</font>
