		<title> Worth OnLine - 96/06-Stocks to Avoid/Stocks to Consider</title>
	</head>
	
	<body background="/imgs/goldbarsmooth.gif" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"
	      text="#000000" link="#FF0000" vlink="#BB0000"> 	
	<a name="#top">
	<table width=550 cellpadding=10 cellspacing=5>
	
	<tr>
		<td width=390 valign=top> 
		
		<a href=/cgi/ad-relay.cgi?http://www.pcfn.com/6015.html?worth+PCFN16.gif+Archives>
<img src="/ads/PCFN16.gif" border=3 width=372 height=45 alt="PC Financial Network"></a>


		</td>
		<td  width=150>
		<!-- empty cell -->
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
	<td width=390 valign=top>
		
		<center>
		<p>
		<b><a href="/index.html">Home</a>  |  <a href="/departments/departments.html">Departments</a>  |  <a href="/search/query.html">Search</a>  |  <a href="/forums/index.html">Message Boards</a></b>
		<pre>
		</pre>
				<font size=5><b></b></font><br>
				<font size=6><b>96/06-Stocks to Avoid/Stocks to Consider</b></font><br>
				<font size=4></font><p>
				</center>
				
				<blockquote>
					<center>
						<font size=4><b><i></i></b></font><p>
					</center>
					<font size=4>
						10 Stocks to Avoid<p>WILL LYONS, a former banker, edits Short on Value, one of only three investment newsletters to focus on picking stocks to sell short. Each issue, Lyons advises his few thousand subscribers to bet against about 30 stocks that he believes are headed for a fall within the next 6 to 12 months because of weak profit margins, heavy debt, or strong competition. For example, shares of broadcaster <a name="NYSE:CCU"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=11824"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>Clear Channel Communications</b></a> have soared since a new law allowed broadcast companies to own more stations. But Clear Channel's "ugly balance sheet," Lyons says, will make it more difficult for the company to fund its strategy of expanding by acquisition. <a name="NASD:EPIC"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=42275"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>Epic Design Technology</b></a>, which sells chip-making software, is valued at 50 times earnings but faces slowing growth in the semiconductor industry. <a name="NASD:INTS"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=14808"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>Integrated Systems</b></a> hopes to provide computer software for machines designed to cost $300 to $500 and provide cheap access to the Internet. Internet mania has propelled the price-to-earnings ratio to 100 -- a lot to pay for a company with unproven technology and an uncertain market. Likewise, Lyons thinks <a name="NASD:IVIP"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=16579"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>IVI Publishing</b></a>, which produces medical CD-ROMs, faces an already overcrowded market.<p>Company          Exchange/Ticker Symbol      Fair Value
*Reasons<p><a name="NASD:ACCS"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=13059"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>Access Health </b></a>               (Nasdaq: ACCS )          $17
*Unsustainable revenue growth 
*Intense competition 
*Outsourcing trend has peaked <p><a name="NASD:AZPN"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=42227"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>Aspen Technology</b></a>           (Nasdaq: AZPN)           $24
*Unsustainable earnings growth 
*Competition is intensifying 
*Private valuation far below public<p><a name="NASD:CUBE"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=17270"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>C-Cube Microsystems</b></a>     (Nasdaq: CUBE)            $29
*Unsustainable revenue growth  
