*Limited market for new product 
*Weak profits <p>IVI Publishing                  (Nasdaq: IVIP)              $7
*Steep R&D costs 
*Limited appeal to consumers   
*Limited sources of revenue   <p><a name="NASD:BEAM"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=17085"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>Summit Technology </b></a>         (Nasdaq: BEAM)          $15
*Unproven product
*Competition is intensifying
*No revenues or earnings<p>
10 Stocks to Consider<p>JOHN BALLEN'S <a name="FUND:MEGBX"></a><a href="http://www.investools.com/cgi-bin/Library/t_page.pl/worth/MEGBX"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>MFS Emerging Growth Fund B</b></a> has ranked in the top 25 percent of small-cap growth funds for five of the past six years, returning a five-year annual average of 24.81 percent. Ballen looks for growth companies that can be major players in their industries in three to five years and buys them when their valuations are below the average for their sectors. For example, Ballen likes <a name="NASD:ADSK"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=12689"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>Autodesk</b></a>, the premier maker of design software for engineers and architects, which took a temporary hit when new products were delayed. He thinks the high costs bedeviling <a name="NYSE:ODP"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=14308"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>Office Depot</b></a> can be fixed easily and expects the stock to rebound in the second half of this year. Ballen is also buying companies with a future in the fast-growing client-server market, such as <a name="NASD:BMCS"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=12708"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>BMC Software</b></a> and <a name="NYSE:CA"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=10383"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>Computer Associates</b></a>. Both are entering the market for software that controls the operations of PC servers. <a name="NYSE:HFS"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=10003"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>HFS</b></a>, the world's largest franchiser of hotels and real-estate brokerages, has increased profits at about 40 percent a year for the past four years. The company cut costs for its Days Inn and other hotel chains by securing low long-distance rates from <a name="NASD:APPB"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=13585"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>AT&T</b></a> and has tripled the value of real-estate brokerage Century 21, which it purchased just last year.<p>Company          Exchange/Ticker Symbol      Fair Value
*Reasons<p><a name="NASD:APPB"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=13585"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>Applebee's Intl</b></a>                 (Nasdaq: APPB)           .$38
*Entering new market
*Strong cash flow from franchises
