		<b><a href="/index.html">Home</a>  |  <a href="/departments/departments.html">Departments</a>  |  <a href="/search/query.html">Search</a>  |  <a href="/forums/index.html">Message Boards</a></b>
		<pre>
		</pre>
				<font size=5><b>Trend Spotter</b></font><br>
				<font size=6><b>96/05-Trend Spotter</b></font><br>
				<font size=4></font><p>
				</center>
				
				<blockquote>
					<center>
						<font size=4><b><i></i></b></font><p>
					</center>
					<font size=4>
						May 1996 <p>Worth magazine/Outfront  <p> TREND SPOTTER  <p> By Monica Corcoran  <p> LEGGO MY LAPTOP. Business travelers, mobile Internet addicts,and anyone else who totes a portable computer, beware. According to computer insurance agency Safeware, PC theft leaped 39 percent last year. "Insurance rates could increase 25 percent in 1997,"says Safeware CEO David Johnston. His advice? "Love your portable."Or someone else will.  <p> OUT OF FASHION. Kurt Salmon Associates reports that 55 percent of shoppers call the latest clothing styles "boring," and 88 percent opt for comfortable wear.     <p> PRIME TIME TO SHOP. Pack up the La-Z-Boy and head to the mall. The Food Court Entertainment Network could be coming to an enclosed shopping center near you, with televisions stationed in food courts broadcasting various programming, including news from CNN, children's shows, sporting events, and, yes, advertisements.  <p> IT AIN'T DISNEYLAND. It seems folks would rather play craps than meet Goofy. According to a nationwide poll of travel agents by Carlson Wagonlit Travel, casinos topped the list of preferred destinations among weekend travelers last summer. That could spell jackpot for New Horizon Kids Quest, a Minneapolis-based company that operates day-care centers at a number of  gambling resorts.  <p> FISCAL INSOMNIA. If you've been tossing and turning over that savings account, you're not alone. One-third of adult Americans lose sleep over money worries, reports the Lutheran Brotherhood.Lack of retirement savings keeps most of us counting sheep, with long-term health-care expenses and insurance angst trailing behind. <p>  <hr>  <p>
KEYWORDS: Technology Industry, Travel Industry
					</font>
					<p>
		
		
		
