				<font size=5><b>Make Mine Mesquite</b></font><br>
				<font size=6><b>96/05-Make Mine Mesquite</b></font><br>
				<font size=4></font><p>
				</center>
				
				<blockquote>
					<center>
						<font size=4><b><i></i></b></font><p>
					</center>
					<font size=4>
						May 1996 <p>Worth magazine/Outfront  <p> MAKE MINE MESQUITE  <p> Kansas City Barbecue Society spokeswoman Carolyn Wells says that barbecue is "an exploding phenomenon -- not literally, we hope." With Memorial Day upon us, here are some easy-to-digest barbecue numbers: Men are 50 percent more likely to work the grill, but whether and what to barbecue are usually a woman's province (women also do the dishes 83 percent of the time). Over three-quarters of U.S. households own grills, which were fired up 2.6 billion times in 1995. Over half of backyard barbecues include music. Most popular tunes? Country and western. <p>
KEYWORDS: Homeowner

					</font>
