				<font size=5><b>Market Radar</b></font><br>
				<font size=6><b>96/05-Market Radar</b></font><br>
				<font size=4></font><p>
				</center>
				
				<blockquote>
					<center>
						<font size=4><b><i></i></b></font><p>
					</center>
					<font size=4>
						May 1996 <p>Worth magazine/Need To Know  <p> MARKET RADAR  <p> After a brief flirtation with optimism last month, the "Market Radar" indicators retreat toward pessimism. The Composite Bellwether index of brokerage and utility stocks heads south again, after failing to match last September's peak. Just as significant, the Advance/Decline Line shifts from positive to neutral as the daily number of stocks losing ground on the New York Stock Exchange catches up to the number advancing. Other markets look worse: On the Nasdaq, declines outpace advances at an alarming rate.  <p> Sources: Advance/Decline Line, Composite Bellwether, and Monetary Exposure Profile from Inves Tech; Advisory Sentiment from Investors Intelligence; Yield Ratio from the Leuthold Group; Consumer and Corporate Debt from Safian Investment Research.   <p>
KEYWORDS: Market Trends<p>

					</font>
