	<tr>
	<td width=390 valign=top>
		
		<center>
		<p>
		<b><a href="/index.html">Home</a>  |  <a href="/departments/departments.html">Departments</a>  |  <a href="/search/query.html">Search</a>  |  <a href="/forums/index.html">Message Boards</a></b>
		<pre>
		</pre>
				<font size=5><b>Zeros are Adding Up</b></font><br>
				<font size=6><b>96/03-Zeros are Adding Up</b></font><br>
				<font size=4></font><p>
				</center>
				
				<blockquote>
					<center>
						<font size=4><b><i></i></b></font><p>
					</center>
					<font size=4>
						March 1996
Worth magazine/Need to Know<p>ZEROS ARE ADDING UP<p>By Bernie Napach<p>Many fixed-income investors are betting that falling interest rates will further boost bond prices. At least that's the hope of investors looking to match the 19.24 percent total return racked up by the <a name="NYSE:LEH"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=41936"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>Lehman Brothers</b></a> government/corporate bond index in 1995.<p>But 30-year rates fell 193 basis points (100 basis points equal one percentage point) last year, and few expect a decline this year of more than an additional 50 basis points. That won't be enough to produce double-digit returns, except for intrepid investors who resort to zero-coupon bonds. Last year, 30-year zero-coupon Treasurys soared more than 60 percent. In 1996 they're the vehicle of choice for investors who want to get the most bang from any fall in interest rates.<p>Zeros pay no interest; there's nothing to cushion the effects of interest-rate swings. When rates rise one percentage point, long-term zeros plummet 30 percent, compared with a 12 percent drop in 30-year, interest-paying Treasurys. But if rates drop 50 basis points, 30-year zeros will gain 22 percent.<p>Only a few mutual funds invest solely in zeros. And the  only fund company offering truly long-term zeros is Twentieth Century's Benham Group (800-331-8331). It has zero funds that mature in 20 or 25 years. <p><p>
KEYWORDS: Bond Investing, Mutual Funds Investing

					</font>
					<p>
		
		
		
</td><td width=150 valign=top>

<center>
		
	<a href="/index.html">
	<IMG SRC="/imgs/datalineyellow.gif" border=0 alt="Worth"></a><p>
