		</td>
		<td  width=150>
		<!-- empty cell -->
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
	<td width=390 valign=top>
		
		<center>
		<p>
		<b><a href="/index.html">Home</a>  |  <a href="/departments/departments.html">Departments</a>  |  <a href="/search/query.html">Search</a>  |  <a href="/forums/index.html">Message Boards</a></b>
		<pre>
		</pre>
				<font size=5><b>Fund Briefs</b></font><br>
				<font size=6><b>95/09-Fund Briefs</b></font><br>
				<font size=4></font><p>
				</center>
				
				<blockquote>
					<center>
						<font size=4><b><i></i></b></font><p>
					</center>
					<font size=4>
						September 1995
Worth magazine/Need To Know<p>FUND BRIEFS<p>By Andrew Gluck<p>FEEING FRENZY: <a name="NYSE:SCH"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=10320"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>Charles Schwab & Co.</b></a> and Fidelity Investments are about to add new fees on small accounts. Beginning October 1, Schwab will assess a $7.50 quarterly fee on accounts with less than a $1,000 balance in three consecutive months. Starting in November, Fidelity will charge a $12 annual fee if an investor has less than $2,500 in any fund--up to a maximum of $60 per customer. Fidelity will waive the fees for accounts above $50,000 and Schwab for customers with $10,000 in all household accounts.<p>XENOFUNDIA: Just 26 percent of U.S. households that own funds invest in international or global funds, according to a poll conducted for Scudder Funds. Of those surveyed, 18 percent--up from 10 percent in the poll a year ago--said funds primarily invested in foreign securities are too risky.<p>FINANCIALLY SOUND? Large concentrations in any sector can add unexpected risk to a portfolio. In mid-July some 21 supposedly diversified equity funds had more than 50 percent of their assets in financial companies, according to data from Morningstar. The 21 include CGM Mutual, Selected American Shares, Clipper, Third Avenue Value, and Legg Mason Total Return Trust.<p><p>
KEYWORDS: Mutual Funds Investing

					</font>
					<p>
		
		
		
</td><td width=150 valign=top>

<center>
		
	<a href="/index.html">
	<IMG SRC="/imgs/datalineyellow.gif" border=0 alt="Worth"></a><p>
