		<title> Worth OnLine - 95/06-Fund Briefs</title>
	</head>
	
	<body background="/imgs/goldbarsmooth.gif" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"
	      text="#000000" link="#FF0000" vlink="#BB0000"> 	
	<a name="#top">
	<table width=550 cellpadding=10 cellspacing=5>
	
	<tr>
		<td width=390 valign=top> 
		
		<a href=/cgi/ad-relay.cgi?http://www.pcfn.com/6007.html?worth+PCFN25.gif+Archives>
<img src="/ads/PCFN25.gif" border=3 width=372 height=45 alt="PC Financial Network"></a>


		</td>
		<td  width=150>
		<!-- empty cell -->
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
	<td width=390 valign=top>
		
		<center>
		<p>
		<b><a href="/index.html">Home</a>  |  <a href="/departments/departments.html">Departments</a>  |  <a href="/search/query.html">Search</a>  |  <a href="/forums/index.html">Message Boards</a></b>
		<pre>
		</pre>
				<font size=5><b>Fund Briefs</b></font><br>
				<font size=6><b>95/06-Fund Briefs</b></font><br>
				<font size=4></font><p>
				</center>
				
				<blockquote>
					<center>
						<font size=4><b><i></i></b></font><p>
					</center>
					<font size=4>
						June 1995 <p>Worth magazine/Need to Know  <p> FUND BRIEFS  <p> By Elizabeth Macdonald  <p> NO WAY OUT: Beware of getting trapped in a mutual fund. Few investors know it, but the SEC allows funds to suspend redemptions in a crisis if they can't meet the demand for withdrawals. Holders of some <a name="NYSE:LEH"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=41936"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>Lehman</b></a> funds with Mexican exposure learned that lesson the hard way when the peso crisis struck: Lehman blocked redemptions in three offshore funds not just for a day but for two weeks. <p> INTO AFRICA: If Mexico's too tame for you, the Calvert Group has introduced the New Africa Fund, a "socially responsible" fund that will invest in companies throughout the continent's14 stock exchanges. Sure, these markets are poorly regulated and face political instabilities. But Justine Beckett, the fund's manager, promises, "We won't be investing in companies operating in riskier markets, such as Somalia, Burundi, or Libya, anytime soon."   <p> DON'T BANK ON IT : Mutual funds will score a small victory overbanks if the IRS succeeds in yanking the tax-deferred status of the Retirement CD, a certificate of deposit that offers $100,000 FDIC insurance and works like an annuity. (Annuities sold by insurers and mutual-fund firms won't be affected.) If the planflies, income from CDs purchased after April 7, 1995, would be taxed in the year earned. Deposits made before that time would remain tax-deferred.    <p>  <p><p>
KEYWORDS: Mutual Funds Investing, International Investing

					</font>
					<p>
		
		
		
</td><td width=150 valign=top>

<center>
		
	<a href="/index.html">
	<IMG SRC="/imgs/datalineyellow.gif" border=0 alt="Worth"></a><p>
</center>
<pre>


</pre>
					<tt><font size=+1>
					<center>
