<html>
	<head>
		<title> Worth OnLine - 95/04-Yes, We Do Windows</title>
	</head>
	
	<body background="/imgs/goldbarsmooth.gif" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"
	      text="#000000" link="#FF0000" vlink="#BB0000"> 	
	<a name="#top">
	<table width=550 cellpadding=10 cellspacing=5>
	
	<tr>
		<td width=390 valign=top> 
		
		<a href=/cgi/ad-relay.cgi?http://www.pcfn.com/6015.html?worth+PCFN16.gif+Archives>
<img src="/ads/PCFN16.gif" border=3 width=372 height=45 alt="PC Financial Network"></a>


		</td>
		<td  width=150>
		<!-- empty cell -->
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
	<td width=390 valign=top>
		
		<center>
		<p>
		<b><a href="/index.html">Home</a>  |  <a href="/departments/departments.html">Departments</a>  |  <a href="/search/query.html">Search</a>  |  <a href="/forums/index.html">Message Boards</a></b>
		<pre>
		</pre>
				<font size=5><b>Yes, We Do Windows</b></font><br>
				<font size=6><b>95/04-Yes, We Do Windows</b></font><br>
				<font size=4></font><p>
				</center>
				
				<blockquote>
					<center>
						<font size=4><b><i></i></b></font><p>
					</center>
					<font size=4>
						April 1995
Worth Magazine/Outfront<p>YES, WE DO WINDOWS<p>Financial gurus have found a new realm to populate: computer software. Soon, whenever you boot up your CD-ROM drive, you may have a recognizable advisor along for the ride in the form of digital photos and sound clips. Andrew Tobias, for example, gazes out from the new version of Block Financial Software's Managing Your Money. Jane Bryant Quinn and Marshall Loeb, meanwhile, are full of gestures and advice in Intuit's latest edition of Quicken. "People want a reassuring voice," says Loeb. "If you're sitting alone working at a computer on your desk, it's nice to have a human face speaking to you." <p>And as long as the subject is money, the emphasis will be on familiar, trustworthy, human faces__not caricatures like Bob, <a name="NASD:MSFT"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=14120"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>Microsoft</b></a>'s planned computer pal. "I'm not sure anyone wants to take personal financial advice from a cartoon rat," says Quinn. "Unless they're cheating on their taxes."<p><p>
KEYWORDS: Technology Industry

					</font>
					<p>
		
		
		
</td><td width=150 valign=top>

<center>
		
	<a href="/index.html">
	<IMG SRC="/imgs/datalineyellow.gif" border=0 alt="Worth"></a><p>
</center>
<pre>


</pre>
					<tt><font size=+1>
					<center>
						<img src="/imgs/1page.gif"><br>About 1 page

					</font>
					</tt>
					</center>

					<pre>
					</pre>


					</font>
