Worth magazine/Outfront<p>GLOBAL CHIC
A checklist of cool for status seekers in Marietta, Georgia<p>- Bringing a picnic dinner to a concert by pop duo Banks & Shane<p>- Stopping by the Georgian Club for lunch with Marietta's most famous resident, Speaker of the House Newt Gingrich<p>- Having seen Lips Together, Teeth Apart, the play that inspired the town to propose a family-values ordinance<p>- Adorning your front porch with a handmade rocker from Marietta's Brumby Chair Company<p>- Scoring 25 kills on the virtual-reality game at Dave & Buster's restaurant<p>- Knowing how to get anywhere from "The Big Chicken," a huge sheet-metal bird with rolling eyes in front of the local Kentucky Fried Chicken<p>

