<html>
	<head>
		<title> Worth OnLine - 94/11-Investors Get Help Gauging Risk</title>
	</head>
	
	<body background="/imgs/goldbarsmooth.gif" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"
	      text="#000000" link="#FF0000" vlink="#BB0000"> 	
	<a name="#top">
	<table width=550 cellpadding=10 cellspacing=5>
	
	<tr>
		<td width=390 valign=top> 
		
		<a href=/cgi/ad-relay.cgi?http://www.pcfn.com/6015.html?worth+PCFN16.gif+Archives>
<img src="/ads/PCFN16.gif" border=3 width=372 height=45 alt="PC Financial Network"></a>


		</td>
		<td  width=150>
		<!-- empty cell -->
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
	<td width=390 valign=top>
		
		<center>
		<p>
		<b><a href="/index.html">Home</a>  |  <a href="/departments/departments.html">Departments</a>  |  <a href="/search/query.html">Search</a>  |  <a href="/forums/index.html">Message Boards</a></b>
		<pre>
		</pre>
				<font size=5><b>Investors Get Help Gauging Risk</b></font><br>
				<font size=6><b>94/11-Investors Get Help Gauging Risk</b></font><br>
				<font size=4></font><p>
				</center>
				
				<blockquote>
					<center>
						<font size=4><b><i></i></b></font><p>
					</center>
					<font size=4>
						November 1994-Worth Magazine
Worth magazine/Need To Know<p>BOND-FUND INVESTORS GET HELP GAUGING RISK<p>By Gregory Millman<p>This year, bond-fund investors have learned about risk the hard way. Since January, taxable bond funds are down 2.97 percent, largely because of an increase in interest rates. But some derivative-laden funds have taken far bigger hits -- for example, the total return of <a name="FUND:PJIGX"></a><a href="http://www.investools.com/cgi-bin/Library/t_page.pl/worth/PJIGX"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>Piper Capital's Institutional Government Income Portfolio</b></a> is down 25.23 percent so far this year because of derivative trading by fund manager Worth Bruntjen. That has left investors scrambling to find out just how risky their funds really are. Prospectuses and fund reports often reveal precious little about a fund's potentially risky securities trades.<p>Two major credit-rating services have recently stepped into this information breach. Standard & Poor's and Fitch Investor Services in New York introduced two new risk-rating systems to analyze the market volatility of bond funds. To calculate the ratings, analysts use sophisticated computer simulations to test how a bond fund will react to prepayments, interest-rate fluctuations, and choppy markets. Fitch rates funds on a scale from V1 through V10 (V for volatility); V1 funds are the least volatile. S&P uses the letters a, b, and c, with an aaa-rated fund carrying the lowest possible risk, and ccc the highest.<p>Not surprisingly, few fund managers are signing on. Managers worry that the threat of a rating downgrade could make it harder for them to earn top returns. So far, Fitch has taken on just over a half-dozen funds, while S&P has just over 50 takers. (S&P is also forcing funds that want to use its credit ratings to carry its risk ratings.) "This is something that benefits investors," says John Schiavetta of Fitch, "and some fund managers are nervous about it." <p>Russell Long, a director of S&P's managed-funds group, says investors can gauge an unrated fund's risk by seeing if gross assets are much higher than net assets, which could mean it is highly leveraged. Also, a big discrepancy between a security's par and market values may indicate a risky derivative sensitive to interest and prepayment rates. <p>-- by Gregory Millman<p>
FUNDS RATED TOPS FOR LOW RISK
---------------
<a name="FUND:SHTIX"></a><a href="http://www.investools.com/cgi-bin/Library/t_page.pl/worth/SHTIX"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>Aim Limited Maturity</b></a>. Risk rating: aaa. Current yield: 3.83 percent.<p><a name="FUND:SBSHX"></a><a href="http://www.investools.com/cgi-bin/Library/t_page.pl/worth/SBSHX"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>Smith Breeden Short Duration U.S. Government</b></a>. Risk rating: aa+. Current yield: 5.04 percent.<p><a name="FUND:MARMX"></a><a href="http://www.investools.com/cgi-bin/Library/t_page.pl/worth/MARMX"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>Midwest Adjustable Rate U.S. Government Securities Fund</b></a>. Risk rating: aa+. Current yield: 3.91 percent.<p><a name="FUND:OEVGX"></a><a href="http://www.investools.com/cgi-bin/Library/t_page.pl/worth/OEVGX"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>Overland Express Variable Rate Government</b></a>. Risk rating: V2. Current yield: 4.30 percent.<p>Source: Standard & Poor's, Fitch Investor Services<p><p><p><p>
KEYWORDS: Mutual Funds Investing
					</font>
