	<head>
		<title> Worth OnLine - 94/10-Fund Mania Goes Global</title>
	</head>
	
	<body background="/imgs/goldbarsmooth.gif" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"
	      text="#000000" link="#FF0000" vlink="#BB0000"> 	
	<a name="#top">
	<table width=550 cellpadding=10 cellspacing=5>
	
	<tr>
		<td width=390 valign=top> 
		
		<a href=/cgi/ad-relay.cgi?http://www.pcfn.com/6007.html?worth+PCFN25.gif+Archives>
<img src="/ads/PCFN25.gif" border=3 width=372 height=45 alt="PC Financial Network"></a>


		</td>
		<td  width=150>
		<!-- empty cell -->
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
	<td width=390 valign=top>
		
		<center>
		<p>
		<b><a href="/index.html">Home</a>  |  <a href="/departments/departments.html">Departments</a>  |  <a href="/search/query.html">Search</a>  |  <a href="/forums/index.html">Message Boards</a></b>
		<pre>
		</pre>
				<font size=5><b>Fund Mania Goes Global</b></font><br>
				<font size=6><b>94/10-Fund Mania Goes Global</b></font><br>
				<font size=4></font><p>
				</center>
				
				<blockquote>
					<center>
						<font size=4><b><i></i></b></font><p>
					</center>
					<font size=4>
						October 1994
Worth magazine/Need to Know<p>FUND MANIA GOES GLOBAL<p>By Monica Corcoran<p>The U.S. market for financial services may be near saturation, but the infant overseas market for mutual funds has just started to explode. Last January, for instance, <a name="NYSE:MS"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=11018"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>Morgan Stanley</b></a>'s Bombay office ran a newspaper ad inviting Indians to invest in their country's first private mutual fund. In just three days an estimated 1 million investors plowed $300 million into the fund -- three times the anticipated offering amount.<p>The boom isn't limited to emerging markets, either. In Europe, aggregate assets held in mutual funds jumped 18.5 percent from 1992 to 1993. <p>American companies are feverishly pushing their products abroad. "All the non-U.S. markets are still evolving, and there's a lot of opportunity over there," says William McBride, international editor at Lipper Analytical Services, a mutual fund tracking firm.<p>The big publicly traded companies for investors to watch include <a name="NYSE:MER"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=10990"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>Merrill Lynch</b></a> (MER), which has 29 mutual funds overseas and a big presence in Japan, Mexico, and Brazil; <a name="NYSE:CCI"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=10345"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>Citicorp</b></a> (CCI), which has 28 funds overseas; and <a name="NYSE:AC"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=43712"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>Alliance Capital Management</b></a> (AC), which has a heavy market presence in Japan, Australia, the United Kingdom, and India. <p><p>
KEYWORDS: International Investing

					</font>
					<p>
		
		
		
</td><td width=150 valign=top>

<center>
		
	<a href="/index.html">
	<IMG SRC="/imgs/datalineyellow.gif" border=0 alt="Worth"></a><p>
</center>
<pre>


</pre>
