	<tr>
	<td width=390 valign=top>
		
		<center>
		<p>
		<b><a href="/index.html">Home</a>  |  <a href="/departments/departments.html">Departments</a>  |  <a href="/search/query.html">Search</a>  |  <a href="/forums/index.html">Message Boards</a></b>
		<pre>
		</pre>
				<font size=5><b>Next: Second-Guesser Suits</b></font><br>
				<font size=6><b>94/10-Next: Second-Guesser Suits</b></font><br>
				<font size=4></font><p>
				</center>
				
				<blockquote>
					<center>
						<font size=4><b><i></i></b></font><p>
					</center>
					<font size=4>
						October 1994
Worth magazine/Need to Know<p>NEXT: SECOND-GUESSER SUITS<p>By Jonathan Burton<p>Sue your mutual fund for making a bad investment? One shareholder is trying it, seeking class-action status for a suit in Illinois against <a name="FUND:SCOBX"></a><a href="http://www.investools.com/cgi-bin/Library/t_page.pl/worth/SCOBX"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>Scudder Global Fund</b></a>. "I don't think anyone views this as a simple nuisance suit," says Larry Rogers of Shereff, Friedman, Hoffman & Goodman, a New York law firm.<p>In the suit, investor Jonathan Panfil says Scudder Global breached its fiduciary duty first by buying shares of software maker Policy Management Systems in the absence of what the suit calls "reliable financial or accounting information," and second by not selling the shares when, the suit alleges, improprieties became public. Panfil wants Scudder and other funds to refund $100 million. <p>Scudder says it didn't know the depth of problems until auditors withdrew their approval of Policy Management's financials in August 1993. Selling then would have sealed a loss, Scudder says. The stock has since risen but is still down 25 percent since Scudder bought it. In the past 12 months, the fund has gained 11.5 percent -- apparently good enough for Panfil. He bought more shares last October and this March.<p><p>
KEYWORDS: Mutual Funds Investing

					</font>
					<p>
		
		
		
</td><td width=150 valign=top>

<center>
		
	<a href="/index.html">
	<IMG SRC="/imgs/datalineyellow.gif" border=0 alt="Worth"></a><p>
</center>
<pre>


</pre>
					<tt><font size=+1>
					<center>
						<img src="/imgs/1page.gif"><br>About 1 page

					</font>
					</tt>
					</center>

					<pre>
					</pre>


					</font>
					<p>

					<p>

<font size=+1><b>Mutual Fund Index</b><br>
</font>						<a href="#FUND:SCOBX">Scudder Global Fund</a><br>

					<p>
	
		
</td>
	</tr>
