	<td width=390 valign=top>
		
		<center>
		<p>
		<b><a href="/index.html">Home</a>  |  <a href="/departments/departments.html">Departments</a>  |  <a href="/search/query.html">Search</a>  |  <a href="/forums/index.html">Message Boards</a></b>
		<pre>
		</pre>
				<font size=5><b>September Tip Sheet</b></font><br>
				<font size=6><b>94/09-September Tip Sheet</b></font><br>
				<font size=4></font><p>
				</center>
				
				<blockquote>
					<center>
						<font size=4><b><i></i></b></font><p>
					</center>
					<font size=4>
						September 1994
Worth magazine/Need to Know<p>SEPTEMBER TIP SHEET<p>-> HELP FOR THE MACINTOSH USER: Until now, you had to use an <a name="NYSE:IBM"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=10796"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>IBM</b></a>-compatible computer to enjoy the benefits of investment software offering both portfolio-management tools and on-line trading. Now <a name="NYSE:SCH"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=10320"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>Charles Schwab</b></a> is selling a Macintosh version of its StreetSmart program for $59, offering unlimited real-time price quotes and trade orders. For a surcharge, users can gain access to Dow Jones news reports and Standard & Poor's data. One drawback: StreetSmart can't translate historical quotes into language that the portfolio-management part of the program can read. Still, StreetSmart is one small step for Mac users. And one big step for Schwab: Rival Fidelity Investments isn't scheduled to have a Mac version of its software until 1995 at the earliest.<p>-> LEASE RELEASE: Watch for an attractive way to buy a used car. This year, thanks to the auto industry's recent love affair with leasing, a record 2 million cars will return to dealers as their leases expire. "By 1997, we'll be swimming in them," says Ted Orme of the National Automobile Dealers Association. Previously leased cars sell for prices comparable to standard used cars. Many dealers recondition postlease cars and re-lease them with full warranties. Look for good deals on two- and three-year old Jaguars.<p>-> WHERE THERE'S NO WILL, THERE'S A WAY: In 19 states it's possible to designate heirs to your securities accounts without writing a will or worrying about probate of your estate. These states have passed the Uniform Transfer on Death Securities Registration Act, which allows nonprobate transfers of stock, bond, and mutual fund accounts without a will. Previously, such transfers were possible for bank accounts but not securities accounts. The law hasn't passed in New York -- home to many of the big brokerage firms -- but it will be reintroduced next year. <p><p>
KEYWORDS: Technology Industry

					</font>
					<p>
		
		
		
</td><td width=150 valign=top>

