				<font size=5><b> </b></font><br>
				<font size=6><b>93/10-New for Fall</b></font><br>
				<font size=4></font><p>
				</center>
				
				<blockquote>
					<center>
						<font size=4><b><i></i></b></font><p>
					</center>
					<font size=4>
						  
Investing has fashions, just like any other industry. Don't get caught in last year's style; check out hwt the well-dressed portfolio is wearing.<p>By Carla Koehl<p>IN:
A surefire trend alert:The mutual fund mavens at Morningstar expect to add a new fund category--telecommunications--to the 23 groupings they track. At least seven funds fit the telecom mold, and all but one are performing well. Morningstar editor John Rekenthaler guesses another five or six will launch soon.<p>OUT:
following 1993's automotive rally, the smart dollars are getting out of Detroit. "Auto stocks have gone about as far as they can go," says Hugh Johnson of First Albany. Among the warning signals:Weak consumer confidence and a late-stage bull market, when car stocks traditionally falter.<p> <p><p><p>
KEYWORDS: Stock Market Trends

					</font>
