				<font size=5><b></b></font><br>
				<font size=6><b>97/02-Investing: Tip Sheet</b></font><br>
				<font size=4></font><p>
				</center>
				
				<blockquote>
					<center>
						<font size=4><b><i></i></b></font><p>
					</center>
					<font size=4>
						WHOSE INFLATION?
Those new inflation-indexed Treasury securities may carry more risk than investors realize. The principal value of the bonds will be adjusted upward with any climb in the consumer price index. But the Boskin commission recently concluded that the CPI overstates inflation and that the index should be recalculated. That would create an even wider gulf between the inflation index and the higher inflation experienced by retirees and parents: Medical costs have recently been rising at more than 4.5 percent a year, while educational costs have been increasing more than 5.5 percent annually. Investors still interested in the new bonds should look for a low-cost fund, such as the new American Century–Benham Treasury Inflation Protection Securities Fund (due out in March, 800-345-2021) or the Dreyfus Inflation Adjusted Securities Fund (800-645-6561).<p>
PLAYING THE SPREAD
Investors trading over-the-counter issues with big spreads -- the difference between the seller's asking price and the buyer's bid price -- have a new way to minimize their costs. Two times a day, discount broker Jack White will use POSIT, the automatic trade-matching system, to pair buyers and sellers -- and split the spread between them. Call 800-233-3411 for more information. <p>
BRIEFS
Michael Murphy, whose California Technology Stock Letter has consistently beaten the Wilshire 5000 Index, is taking over management of three <a name="FUND:MNTGX"></a><a href="http://www.investools.com/cgi-bin/Library/t_page.pl/worth/MNTGX"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>Monitrend Funds</b></a>, renaming them Murphy Technology Fund, Murphy Biotechnology Fund, and Murphy New World Convertible Fund (415-726-8495)....Brian Posner, the highly successful manager of Fidelity's <a name="FUND:FEQTX"></a><a href="http://www.investools.com/cgi-bin/Library/t_page.pl/worth/FEQTX"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>Equity-Income II Fund</b></a>, is leaving to join the <a HREF="http://www.wechsler.com/portfolio/warburg/warburg1.html">Warburg Pincus Fund group</A>. Posner's replacement is Bettina Doulton, manager of <a name="FUND:FPURX"></a><a href="http://www.investools.com/cgi-bin/Library/t_page.pl/worth/FPURX"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>Fidelity Puritan</b></a>....Beware the "teaser rates" on Michael Price's Mutual Series Funds (recently renamed the Franklin Mutual Series Funds). Class II shares charge a 1 percent front-end load and 0.25 percent 12b-1 fee for the first 13 months -- but the 12b-1 fee jumps to 1 percent after that.<p>
KEYWORDS:
mutual fund, invest, bond

					</font>
