				<font size=5><b></b></font><br>
				<font size=6><b>96/10-Is This the Time to Buy Beat Up Stocks?</b></font><br>
				<font size=4></font><p>
				</center>
				
				<blockquote>
					<center>
						<font size=4><b><i></i></b></font><p>
					</center>
					<font size=4>
						By Amy Barrett<p>
It's a matter of potential risk and reward. On July 25, all the stocks below were down at least 50 percent from their 52-week highs. To find out how far each might rebound if Wall Street is right about its future, we multiplied the consensus estimate for earnings per share for the next four quarters by the estimate of the rate of earnings growth. To figure out how low each could go if earnings disappoint, we multiplied the earnings estimate by the stock's lowest annual price-to-earnings ratio in the past five years.<p>
